  "body": "I'm trying to use React in a node-webkit project, but there is a problem with `input` element. If a module exports a component containing a `input`, a \"TypeError: Cannot read property 'firstChild' of undefined\" error will be thrown when using it.\n\ncode:\n\n```\n# @cjsx React.DOM\n\nReact = require \"react\"\n\nmodule.exports = React.createClass {\n    render: ->\n      <input type=\"text\" value=\"Hello!\" />\n}\n```\n\n```\nTest= require \"./js/components/test\"\n\nApp = React.createClass {\n  render: ->\n    <Test />\n}\n\nReact.render <App />, document.body\n```\n\nThis piece of code works fine if I replace `input` with `textarea` or other elements or just write `Test` and `App` in the same file.\n",
